@DataBase Dev_Changes_To_V1.10.guide

@Node Main "Internal Changes to HydraBBS between V1.07 and V1.10"

  *** Developer Information ***

  This document is stored as:

    HBBS:Developer/Docs/Upgrades/Dev_Changes_V1.10.guide


  If you have written some doors or are going to write some, then please
  read the following information:


  Internal Changes to HydraBBS between V1.07 and V1.10
  ====================================================

  * HBBSCommon.library and HBBSNode.library

    Autodocs updated.

  * Defines.h

    oh blimey, I fudged up the defines for the getline flags and the
    continue prompt flags.  All the old doors will have worked until
    they were re-compiled... to be exact (1<<x) should have been
    (1 << x-1 ).  The defines have now been recified and tested..

    Sorry to any door coders experiancing problems...

  * Node

    Doors that call DOOR_HangUp() will cause the node to display
    the message "Hanging Up" in the watch window (only the sysop will
    see the message).

  * Logout

    Now does not allow other Logout doors to run if the user cancels
    the logout request if they still had flagged files.

  * Also, for a limited period, you can get the source code for free if you
    are going to write some doors, please see the @{"web-site" link HBBS:HBBS.Guide/Website} or @{"e-mail" link HBBS:HBBS.Guide/email} me
    for details.

  * Control and Node

    Both programs now check for the correct version of the HBBSCommon.library
    and HBBSNode.library using the defines in includes/hbbs/release.h
    called HBBSCOMMONVERSION, HBBSCOMMONREVISION, HBBSNODEVERSION,  and
    HBBSREVISION.

    The revision if checked *after* the library is opened (as you can only
    specify a version when you call OpenLibrary().

    I strongly advise all door coders to do this too.

    (However, the door won't ever be started if the versions are *too* old
    because control and node won't have started in the first place :-)

  * HBBSCommon.library

    strNcpy with a length of 0 would actually copy 1 byte, fixed.

    Set libversion to 1 and librevision to 10.

    HBBS_AddCfgItem() always returned FALSE, fixed, it now returns
    TRUE or FALSE.

    Added HBBS_AddCfgList() which is used to add a linked list to
    a config file (so you can read in a stringlist or pathlist
    from a config file, update it and write it back again)
    See the autodocs

  * HBBSNode.library

    Set libversion to 1 and librevision to 10.

@EndNode

